      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-2C243796-C766-48A0-81FB-F7AD20FCA055" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>AUTOMATION Tool will create Intel Lots in MES/WS from WH into factory for the bailed lots. For customers not specifying bailed lots, tool selects lot based on FIFO approach.
Kitting System will dictate MES on what material lot (IDs) needs to be consumed in which production lots. Kitting instruction will have access to staged Build instructions.
MES should not create Lot before ABR instruction. . 
MES will feed SO Line-Item Attribute while sending signal for Production Order creation. 
Sales Order Line Item associated with Production Order is further tracked in manufacturing system for lot visibility
Production order release is going to trigger outbound delivery and goods Issue process (including bailed material)
Pick  identified Inventory against prod order and consume in Manufacturing  Process
At the end of a mfg. stage (say WLA), Intel Foundry will sell the product at that time to customer with value added price but keep material physically for executing next steps. And Then on final mfg. stage, sell Finished good with delta valued added price.



</text>
      </textAnnotation>
